Write a program for Insert Trigger and explain

An INSERT trigger is a special SQL block that automatically runs when a new record is inserted into a table.

CREATE TABLE Students (
    StudentID INT,
    Name VARCHAR(50),
    Marks INT
);

CREATE TABLE Student_Log (
    LogID INT IDENTITY(1,1),
    StudentID INT,
    Action VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TRIGGER trg_AfterInsertStudent
ON Students
AFTER INSERT
AS
BEGIN
    INSERT INTO Student_Log (StudentID, Action)
    SELECT StudentID, 'Inserted'
    FROM inserted;
END;

INSERT INTO Students VALUES (1, 'Ravi', 80);

An INSERT trigger is a database object that automatically executes after a record is inserted into a table.
